{
  "stem": "27390.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So, as a child, I didn't take much notice of these things.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Except sometimes they used to call me, children used to call me [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], things like that, which is not a very nice compliment.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So that's when I didn't like it but otherwise, it didn't bother me very much.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But my people, grown-ups-- for instance, if a-- if a Jew wanted his son to start at university, he had to send him abroad because there was a quota in-- in how many Jews are allowed in Polish universities.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So normally, a Jew, unless he was very rich, could not have his child, his son or his daughter study in a university unless he could afford to send them to abroad.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Lots of things like that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "For instance, a Jew could not open a business unless he-- first of all, every year you had to have, it was called a patent, such a certificate to open a shop or-- or a factory.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then you had to have-- see, every trade had a guild.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You could not start a business unless you had the certificate from this particular guild.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And these guilds, were-- a Jew could not normally get the certificate from such a guild, unless he employed a macher.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "A macher was called a man, a Jew, who knew somebody in the government that was connected with this particular guild and he bribed him and then he could get such a certificate to start a business.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "A lot of things like that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It was very hard to-- to start a business but somehow, we managed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It must have been about 1935, 1936, my father wanted to leave.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
